cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.PL, cs.CR

This paper focuses on the failure of modern open source projects and the reasons behind it. It discusses the maintenance practices and strategies used by developers to overcome project failure. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
